reviewText:
Let's be clear, this game is awesome, it really is, but it will be HARD to finish.
Everything is fine until the last section of levels, in the high security area. I've encountered incredible amounts of bugs, making me unable to finish.

In the last areas:
- Lara does not aim at enemies with her weapon (she has only one in these levels by the way), needless to say this bug makes it annoying to shoot at enemy with rafle mode selected, ending up wasting ammo;
- Lara got stuck in a cinematic, making her unable to get her weapon back;
- Lara got stuck in the elevator area, leading to death up or down;
- The first cyborg got immortal, revealing his electric arm and releasing water didn't kill him;
- Basically, saving and loading in the last area is VERY bad idea, most of spots are bugged.

Other than that, I really do love this game, especially the Rome area, because we get to kill giant statues. We love moving statues. And when we get to play Lara as a teenager. A terrifying set of levels, with no guns and creepy creatures.

There are few ways to go past these bugs if you look around on the internet (check out Stella's website for example). But I still haven't figure out how to solve the problem with the gun automatic aim.

I do recommend it though! Even if it's not as good as the other series.

(The screenshots shown in the preview are wrong though, Lara is not going in Egypt in this game!)
